subtasks.details:
Create src/components/BoardQuestionView.tsx component that renders BoardQuestionContent: vignetteHtml in styled container, questionStemHtml, answers[] with letter/html/isCorrect/peerPercent display, explanationHtml and keyPointsHtml as expandable sections, images with localPath rendering, and collapsible Attempts (N) badge showing attempts[] history. Add HTML rendering with safe styling (no sanitization per spec). Update user's Tampermonkey script to change target port to 23847, ensure it POSTs CapturePayload format with pageHTML and images[] to /api/capture endpoint. Add error handling and user feedback in script.
<info added on 2026-01-08T21:43:48.551Z>
I'll analyze the codebase to provide specific implementation guidance for the BoardQuestionView component.Based on my codebase analysis, here's the update text for the subtask focusing only on the BoardQuestionView React component:

---

COMPONENT STRUCTURE:
- Import shadcn/ui components: Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardContent (src/components/ui/card.tsx), Badge (src/components/ui/badge.tsx), Collapsible/CollapsibleTrigger/CollapsibleContent (src/components/ui/collapsible.tsx)
- Import Tailwind utility: cn from @/lib/utils
- Follow existing component patterns from src/components/cards/CardBrowserView.tsx and src/components/review/ReviewInterface.tsx

INTERFACE DEFINITION (based on docs/HANDOFF-T124.md lines 54-98):
```typescript
interface BoardQuestionContent {
  source: 'peerprep' | 'mksap';
  questionId?: string;
  category?: string;
  capturedAt: string;
  sourceUrl: string;
  vignetteHtml: string;
  questionStemHtml: string;
  answers: {
    letter: string;
    html: string;
    isCorrect: boolean;
    isUserChoice: boolean;
    peerPercent?: number;
  }[];
  wasCorrect: boolean;
  explanationHtml: string;
  keyPointsHtml?: string;
  images: {
    localPath: string;
    caption?: string;
    location: 'vignette' | 'explanation' | 'keypoint';
  }[];
  attempts: {
    attemptNumber: number;
    date: string;
    chosenAnswer: string;
    wasCorrect: boolean;
    note?: string;
  }[];
}
```

RENDER LAYOUT (reference design from docs/HANDOFF-T124.md lines 210-241):
1. Card wrapper with header showing source badge, category, date, result indicator (✓/❌), and collapsible Attempts(N) badge
2. Vignette section with vignetteHtml rendered via dangerouslySetInnerHTML, styled with prose class
3. Question stem section with questionStemHtml
4. Answers grid showing letter, html content, peer percentage bar chart, correct checkmark, user selection dot
5. Collapsible sections for Explanation (explanationHtml) and Key Points (keyPointsHtml) using Collapsible components
6. Image rendering: filter images by location field and display inline in respective sections using localPath

HTML RENDERING:
- Use dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: content }} for all HTML fields per spec requirement (no sanitization)
- Apply Tailwind prose classes for medical content typography
- Images: <img src={`file://${app.getPath('userData')}/images/${localPath}`} /> pattern

STYLING:
- Follow existing component styling patterns from CardBrowserView.tsx
- Use Badge variants (secondary, destructive, outline) for metadata display
- Result indicator: green CheckCircle2 icon for correct, red XCircle for incorrect
- Answer grid: flex layout with hover states, peer percentage as horizontal bar using Tailwind width utilities

ATTEMPTS BADGE:
- Collapsible component toggled by Badge with Attempts(N) text
- CollapsibleContent shows attempts[] array in reverse chronological order
- Display format: "Attempt {N} - {date} - {chosenAnswer} - {✓/❌} {note?}"
</info added on 2026-01-08T21:43:48.551Z>
